<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="104" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d104">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/13369</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                President <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-31">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 31, 1918</hi>
                                </date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: I have just received
                            the enclosed telegram<note n="3" xml:id="d104fn1">Telegram No. 129, Aug.
                                30, 1918, from the Diplomatic Liaison Officer with the Supreme War
                                Council, <ref target="frus1918Supp01v01#pg_301">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, supp. 1, vol.
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 301</ref>.</note> which
                            appears to me to be extremely important on account of the necessity of
                            action here in case the policy is adopted. I would be glad if you would
                            tell me your views Tuesday after Cabinet meeting.</p>
                        <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>